== Spiced Cauliflower Steaks ==

Trim the stem end of the @cauliflower{1}, leaving the core intact. Remove the leaves.

Using a large #knife{}, cut the cauliflower in half from top to bottom.

Cut each half into 2 thick 'steaks' per person. Don't worry about any bits that fall off, we'll use them too! Pop the @ground cumin{2%tsp}, @ground turmeric{1.5%tsp}, @ground ginger{½%tsp} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} into a #mixing bowl{}. Mix well.

== Roasting and Assembly ==

Add the cauliflower to the bowl. Rub the mixture evenly onto both sides of the cauliflower (and any smaller bits that fell off!). Make sure they are evenly coated. Season well with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> TIP: Wear rubber gloves to prevent staining your hands!

Transfer to a lined #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} for ~{10-15%minutes}.

> TIP: They are ready when a knife can easily be stuck through the thickest part.

== Protein Packed Salad ==

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest the @lemon{1} and cut into four wedges. Roughly chop the @dried apricots{40%g}. Cook the @brown rice & quinoa{1%packet} in the #microwave{} according to pack instructions.

Pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g} into a small #bowl{}. Mix in the @wholegrain mustard{½%tsp}, half the coriander and the @olive oil{for the dressing}. Season with a large pinch of lemon zest, salt and pepper.

Carefully pop the rice into another large mixing bowl. Stir in the @cumin seeds{½%tsp}, @sunflower seeds{25%g}, @raisins{40%g}, dried apricots, and the rest of the chopped coriander and lemon zest. Season well with a squeeze of lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.

== Serving ==

Divide the mixed grain salad between your plates. Using a #spatula{}, carefully lay the cauliflower steaks and florets on top. Serve the steaks with a nice dollop of the yogurt dressing drizzled over the top. ENJOY!